", "pottery", "video recordings", "societies, etc", "self-employed", "digital photographs", "age and employment", "home-based businesses"], "timestamp": "2026-01-31T21:04:46.792Z", "title": "Robert Blue and Susan Blue Galloway interview conducted by Meredith McGriff, 2018-10-01", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020655686/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2020655687", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020655687/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/c99d0b83-f95d-5ca6-8874-2054c92b6032", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2018030.afc2018030_05060_mv01", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05060_mv/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05060_ph/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05060_ms01/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05060_ms02/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2018030.afc2018030_05060_mv01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["occupational folklife project", "hershberger, keith", "mcgriff, meredith a. e."], "date": "2018", "dates": ["2018"], "description": ["Potter Keith Hershberger discusses his career, starting with his education, early work experiences (including teaching art and working for a production potter), and his recent shift to full-time production work. He also talks about his time as a co-op member at Union Project, and his involvement in the establishment of the Highland Park Pottery Tour with other local potters. He describes his current work, including how he sells his work and his arrangement sharing a studio with three other area potters."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-01-31T20:11:15.128Z", "group": ["catalog-split-09", "catalog", "afc/2018030", "main-catalog-split-09", "production-potters"], "hassegments": true, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020655687/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2018030/afc2018030_05060/afc2018030_05060_mv.jpg", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-serv