 keith", "home-based businesses"], "timestamp": "2026-01-31T21:04:46.792Z", "title": "Keith Hershberger interview conducted by Meredith McGriff, 2018-10-15", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020655687/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2020655688", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020655688/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/8f8ffc2f-9092-55a6-92d8-cdfbb36b9837", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2018030.afc2018030_05080_sr01", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05080_sr01/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05080_sr02/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05080_ph/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05080_ms01/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2018030.afc2018030_05080_ms02/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2018030.afc2018030_05080_sr01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["occupational folklife project", "vanden brink, jenna", "mcgriff, meredith a. e."], "date": "2018", "dates": ["2018"], "description": ["Jenna Vanden Brink talks about her career as a potter. She explains that she became interested after seeing her father work with clay, then pursued an art degree. After working for many years for the ceramics program at Union Project, a community art center, she made the shift to working full-time in clay. She describes the ways her work has developed, how she sells her pots, and what it is like to share a studio with other area potters. She also talks about helping to start the Highland Park Pottery Tour."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-01-31T20:09:31.065Z", "group": ["catalog-split-10", "catalog", "afc/2018030", "main-catalog-split-10", "production-potters"], "hassegments": true, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020655688/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:afc:afc2018030:afc2018030_05080:afc2018030_05080_ph:afc2018030_05080_ph01/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:afc:afc2018030:afc2018030_05080:afc2018030_05080_ph:afc2018030_05080_ph01/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=210&w=316", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:afc:afc2018030:afc2018030_05080:afc2018030_05080_ph:afc2018030_05080_ph01/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=421&w=632", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:afc:afc2018030:afc2018030_05080:afc2018030_05080_ph:afc2018030_05080_ph01/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=843&w=1265", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:afc:afc2018030:afc2018030_05080:afc2018030_05080_ph:afc2018030_05080_ph01/full/pct:50/0/default.jpg#h=1687&w=2531", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:afc:afc2018030:afc2018030_05080:afc2018030_05080_ph:afc2018030_05080_ph01/full/pct:100/0/default.jpg#h=3375&w=5062"], "index": 11, "language": ["english"], "location": ["middle west", "pittsburgh", "united states", "pennsylvania"], "mime_type": ["audio/mp3", "audio/wav", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2", "application/x-audio"], "number": ["2020655688", "2021-02-09t17:18:22", "online resource", "2026-01-21t22:38:14"], "online_format": ["audio", "pdf", "image"], "original_format": ["film, video", "sound recording"], "partof": ["occupational folklife project", "catalog", "american folklife center", "production potters of the midwest: archie green fellows project, 2018-2019"], "score": 21.80604, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2020655688", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["quality of work life", "vanden brink, jenna", "potters", "pennsylvania", "interviews", "personal narratives", "working mothers", "united states", "material culture", "nonprofit organizations", "pottery craft", "work and family", "work ethic", "technological innovations", "art pottery", "quality control", "oral histories", "employees", "folklore", "sound recordings", "career changes", "middle west", "artists' studios", "work-life balance", "color", "job satisfaction", "pottery industry", "pottery", "societies, etc", "self-employed", "digital photographs", "home-based businesses"], "timestamp": "2026-01-31T21:04:46.792Z", "title": "Jenna Vanden Brink interview conducted by Meredith McGriff, 2018-10-15", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020655688/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01/data/sn78000533/00340580357/1949031001/0389.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01:data:sn78000533:00340580357:1949031001:0384/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01/data/sn78000533/00340580357/1949031001/0389.pdf", "segment_count": 6, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78000533/1949-03-10/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01/data/sn78000533/00340580357/1949031001/0389.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01:data:sn78000533:00340580357:1949031001:0384/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01/data/sn78000533/00340580357/1949031001/0389.pdf", "segment_count": 6, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78000533/1949-03-10/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01/data/sn78000533/00340580357/1949031001/0389.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78000533/1949-03-10/ed-1/?sp=6"], "batch": ["ohi_jasmine_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/ohio/", "2/united states/ohio/columbiana/", "3/united states/ohio/columbiana/east liverpool/"], "contributor": ["ohio history connection, columbus, oh"], "date": "1949-03-10", "dates": ["1949-03-10"], "description": ["PAGE SIX lr The bitter battle on the Senate floor was openly predicted at the close of the session of the Senate Labor Committee which approved the TrumanThomas bill The vote was along partisan lines eight Democrats voting against five Re publicans and the Republicans loosed a blast of anguish after it was over After Sen Elbert Thomas the committee chairman announced the vote andsaid the bill was being moved along as the American peo ple had demanded Sen Robert Taft R Ohio called it the most highhanded procedure I have ever seen in Congress He said he had at least 19 amendments to the bill he wanted to offer and he knew that Sen Wayne Morse R Ore had as many more he wanted to offer Thomas told newsmen it was ob vious the committee could go on until doomsday considering amend ments if he let the Republicans have their way There have been repeated asser tions by observers here that the Administration does not have the votes to pass the Thomas Bill as it stands and repeal the TH Act without some kind of compromise The committee vote along party lines meant that the Democratic majority chose to"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-09-04T23:21:30.791Z", "group": ["ndnp/ohi", "ohio-historical-society-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78000533/1949-03-10/ed-1/?sp=6", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01:data:sn78000533:00340580357:1949031001:0389/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=273&w=219", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01:data:sn78000533:00340580357:1949031001:0389/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=547&w=438", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_jasmine_ver01:data:sn78000533:00340580357:1949031001